      • getSnr

        float getSnr()
        Gets SNR of the processed images from result, it is a very important criteria to determine if the returned result is good or not for application. The following are possible values of SNR

        • 100 indicates SNR is good
        • -100 indicates SNR is invalid
        • -90 face-checker has failed (non-human face detected)
        • -91 face-checker has failed (non-live face detected)
        • Float.NaN if there is no SNR

        The application is free to decide its own strategy to cancel/continue the measurement and keep/discard the result according to the SNR values. Here is an example:

        • if 3rd result SNR is -100, cancel the measurement and discard result
        • if 3rd result SNR is -90, continue the measurement and keep result
        • if 3rd result SNR is -91, cancel the measurement and discard result
        • from 4th result if two consecutive SNRs are all -100, cancel the measurement and discard result
        • from 4th result if the SNR is -90 or -91, cancel the measurement and discard result
        Returns:
        a value representing the SNR value
